               <persName xml:id="name1511-2" xml:lang="en">Jonas of Anbar</persName>
               <persName xml:id="name1511-3" xml:lang="en">Yawnan the foreigner</persName>
               <persName xml:id="name1511-4" xml:lang="fr" source="#bibl1511-2">Jonas d’Anbar</persName>
               <persName xml:id="name1511-5" xml:lang="fr-x-fiey" source="#bibl1511-1">YAWNĀN L'ETRANGER</persName>
               <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/person/1511</idno>
               <idno type="FIEY">456</idno>
               <sex value="M" source="#bibl1511-1">male</sex>
               <floruit source="#bibl1511-1"
                        notBefore="0300"
                        syriaca-computed-start="0300"
                        notAfter="0400"
                        syriaca-computed-end="0400">0300-0400</floruit>
               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl1511-1">Yawnan mourut dans son couvent d'al-Anbar. AMS, I, 466-525 ; BHO, 527- 30. Suhadii', II, 143- 75. BSO, II, 1354- 55 (J.M. Fiey) . Sur le christianisme dans le Golfe : Fiey, "Dioceses", 177-219, et les decouvertes recentes a Kharg et Faylaka (Kuwait).</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Yawnān Nūkhriṭā (the "stranger") was born Yuwanis in a noble family of the lineage of Constantine. He became a disciple of Mar Awgin. He changed his name to Yawnan. He journeyed to Jerusalem and Sqete. Awgin sent him to the land of the Persians, and he founded the monastery at Peroz Shapur on the Euphrates (Al-Anbar).</note>
               <bibl xml:id="bib1511-1">
                  <title level="m" xml:lang="la">Biblioteca Hagiographica Syriaca electronica</title>
                  <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/649"/>
                  <citedRange unit="entry"/>
               </bibl>
               <bibl xml:id="bib1511-2">
                  <title level="m" xml:lang="fr">Saints Syriaques</title>
                  <title level="a" xml:lang="fr">YAWNĀN L'ETRANGER</title>
                  <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/650"/>
                  <citedRange unit="entry">456</citedRange>
               </bibl>
               <note>Yawnan died in his monastery in al-Anbar.</note>
               <bibl xml:id="bib1511-4">
                  <title>AMS</title>
                  <citedRange>I, 466-525</citedRange>
               </bibl>
